{
  "text": "Most other studies of germline polymorphisms and renal-cell carcinoma assessed associations between SNPs and the risk of developing cancer, rather than recurrence. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Most of the previously reported polymorphisms were included in our analysis but were not associated with risk of recurrence. We are not aware of previous germline studies of MET polymorphisms and cancer risk or prognosis.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "13770376",
